# PromptCraft
Overview
PromptCraft is a professional web-based tool designed to help users generate effective prompts for various AI models including ChatGPT, DALL-E, Midjourney, Stable Diffusion, and Google Bard. With its clean, responsive interface and intuitive design, PromptCraft simplifies the process of creating well-structured AI prompts for content creators, developers, and AI enthusiasts.

Features
Support for multiple AI models (ChatGPT, DALL-E, Midjourney, etc.)

Customizable prompt parameters (type, style, tone, creativity level)

Real-time prompt preview

Example prompts for inspiration

Copy to clipboard functionality

Responsive design that works on mobile, tablet, and desktop

Modern blue and white theme

Toast notifications for user feedback

No backend required (runs entirely in the browser)

Requirements
PromptCraft is a frontend application that requires only a modern web browser to run. There are no server-side dependencies.

Browser Compatibility
Chrome (recommended)

Firefox

Safari

Edge

Installation
Option 1: Direct File Opening
Download all project files

Open index.html in any modern web browser

Option 2: Web Server Deployment
For best performance, deploy to a web server:

Upload all files to your web server

Ensure the file structure is maintained

Access via your domain (e.g., www.yourdomain.com/promptcraft)

Option 3: Local Development Server
For developers who want to modify the code:

Ensure you have Node.js installed

Install a simple HTTP server: npm install -g http-server

Navigate to the project directory

Run: http-server

Open your browser to the provided local address (typically http://localhost:8080)

File Structure
promptcraft/
├── index.html          # Main application file
├── css/
│   └── style.css      # All styles (also embedded in index.html)
├── js/
│   └── script.js      # All JavaScript (also embedded in index.html)
├── assets/
│   ├── icons/         # Icon assets (using Font Awesome CDN)
│   └── images/        # Additional images (if any)
└── README.txt         # This file


Customization Guide
Changing the Color Theme
To modify the color scheme, edit the CSS variables in the :root selector:
:root {
    --primary: #1a73e8;       /* Main blue color */
    --primary-light: #e8f0fe; /* Light blue */
    --secondary: #4285f4;     /* Secondary blue */
    /* Add your custom colors here */
}


Adding New AI Models
To add support for additional AI models:

1.Edit the AI Model dropdown in the HTML:
<select id="ai-model">
    <!-- Existing options -->
    <option value="new-model">New Model Name</option>
</select>

2.Add model-specific instructions in the JavaScript generatePrompt function:
const modelIntros = {
    // Existing models
    'new-model': 'Introduction text for the new model',
};


Modifying Example Prompts
Edit the examples object in JavaScript to add or modify example prompts:
const examples = {
    // Existing examples
    4: {
        topic: "Your new topic",
        type: "appropriate-type",
        style: "appropriate-style",
        tone: "appropriate-tone"
    }
};


Adding New Prompt Types
To add new prompt types:

1.Add to the Prompt Type dropdown:
<select id="prompt-type">
    <!-- Existing options -->
    <option value="new-type">New Type</option>
</select>

2.Add type-specific instructions:
const typeInstructions = {
    // Existing types
    'new-type': `Instruction template for the new type`,
};


Customizing Styles
The application uses CSS variables for easy customization. Key elements to style:

Header: .header class

Cards: .controls, .preview, and .examples classes

Buttons: .btn class

Form elements: select, input, textarea selectors

Usage Instructions
1.Select your target AI model from the dropdown

2.Choose the type of prompt you want to generate

3.Enter your topic or subject

4.Adjust style, tone, and creativity settings as needed

5.Click "Generate Prompt" to create your customized prompt

6.Use "Copy to Clipboard" to copy the generated prompt

7.Explore example prompts for inspiration


Browser Support
PromptCraft supports all modern browsers that implement:

ES6 JavaScript features

CSS Flexbox and Grid

Clipboard API

